<tr><td colspan=2 Bgcolor=#000000 Align=center><font color=white size=+2>The end is coming.</font>
</td></tr><tr><td width=10% Bgcolor=#101010 Align=center Valign=top><table width=200><tr><td align=center><font size=-1><table><tr><td align=center><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_top.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_left.jpg><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/portraits/SSETHLORTH.jpg width="104" height="184"><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_right.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_bottom.jpg></td></tr></table>Legendary  SSETHLORTH<br>Level 65 Necromancer<br><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_11.gif" title="Silver Order of Leadership"><br>Raid Commander<br><a style="text-decoration:none;" href="main.cgi?fetch=SSETHLORTH"><font size=-1 color="#DDDDDD">SSETHLORTH</font></a><font size=-1>'S LINEAGE</font><br><img src='http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/bio.gif' border=0></font></td></tr></table></td><td width=90% Valign=top><a href=main.cgi?followup=254&forum=4><p align=right><font color=#cccccc>Reply | </a><a href=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/guild-builder/call/main.cgi?action=messages&forum=4><font color=#cccccc>Return</a></p><br clear=all><p><i>/sigh <br><br>I have been hearing about the recent revamp on Stormhammer and am not happy. Soon, you all be about to see some of the things I have seen ..kinda <br><br>For those who have never been there, and think those of us who have been there don't want the change because we like the zone quiet, thats not it at all.. This of a place where:<br><br>You see a pull down the hall, leave your group to go tag it, start running back and find out you had passed through a one way invisible wall and can't get back!!! DOH!<br><br>You run through the woods and grumpy trees throw angry pansies at you!<br><br>You are stuck in a room with 10 doors and none of them open, and 9 out of 10 spin you around and drop you back in the same room and only 1 of them will port you out and you land in another room where a picture on the wall is actually a fake wall to get out.<br><br>You aggro a treasure chest and 8 hobbits come beating on you with Bamsticks.<br><br>You hail a NPC named 'Life' and it death touches you.<br><br>The guards are skunks named Guard McSprinkles and Guard McSpray. Or a skunk named 'Debbis the Fish'?<br><br>NPC's name 'Not Mine' and 'Not Yours' and 'Dinner'? Puller tells the group: "Dinner incoming! One per tell!"<br><br>Oh and to get to your favorite camp, you pass through a fake wall, pass through another fake wall, past a ratman names 'Chuckles' and click on a picture that puts you in a room with no way out except for clicking on a flower pot.<br><br>Or how about a giant hand that likes knock-knock jokes? And when you tell him one he hits you for a knockback that tosses you through a fake wall down a long hallway?<br><br>Or how about hopping up on a table with a chess board and ending up IN a giant chessboard? And when you hop on the giant chessboard you end up in a giant maze where you find rooms that are upside down??<br><br>Or walking around a set of rooms that grow in size, making you feel like Alice in Wonderland.<br><br>All of these things and much more makes PoM unique. All of these fun things are not something you could do with KoS mobs everywhere. You'd never find a group with the guts to do a crawl that deep into a zone that is as complex as PoM. <br><br>They seem to have taken out all the quests...though most where broken...instead of fixing. Gone will be the cool named NPC's like "You" & "Shall" & "Not" & "Pass". KoS mobs will litter the zone. The only good change is the portal location...it is moving from nToV to GD. <br><br>Well, ..nuff said about my rant. I'll still give tours to all with a passion for adventure. Catch ya all later.<br clear=all></i><br></td></tr><tr><td>
</td>
